name: Division of Unity I
description:
'Division of Unity I' is part of a series that explores the division of the sphere and emergent phenomena.
 
The complete perfection and oneness of a sphere has infinity in its finite nature and invites division as all realities cascade from its potential.

The tension between the geometric surface and the undulating organic pulse of the form highlights the myriad permutations of algorithmic growth found in nature from the formation of crystals to the branching of plants.

'Division of Unity' surveys physical forces, prying under their charade of manifestation to uncover the underlying code that connects us to each other and the cosmos.
